verbose_text: Finally, it was demonstrated that EZH2 inhibition exhibited a similar role with miR-144-3p mimics, whereas the overexpression of EZH2 abolished the tumor suppressive effect of miR-144-3p mimics on OSCC cells, suggesting that the EZH2 oncogene mediates the role of miR-144-3p in OSCC.
evidence: EZH2 oncogene mediates the role of miR-144-3p
